article.headline: Old Dominion 81, William & Mary 60
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Valdas Vasylius had 21 points and eight rebounds and Alex Loughton added 17 points Thursday night as Old Dominion beat William & Mary 81-60. The Monarchs (17-7, 10-4 Colonial Athletic Association) led 40-29 at halftime and opened the second half with a 23-8 run to lead 63-37 with just over 10 minutes left. Calvin Baker scored 12 points and Taylor Mokris 11 for the Tribe (7-15, 2-11). Old Dominion built its lead as high as 31 on two occassions in the second half and improved to 11-1 at the Constant Center. ODU shot 54.5 percent in the second half. Abdi Lilonde added 12 points and eight rebounds and Arnand Dahi scored 10 for the Monarchs, which had a season-high 28 assists on 34 baskets.
